<?xml version="1.0"?>
<block>
    <name>Pulse Generator</name>
    <key>PulseGenerator</key>
    <category>Guided Scrambling</category>
    <import>import gr_gs as gs</import>
    <make>gs.PulseGenerator($samplesPerSymbol, $constellation, $baudRate, $numberOfTaps, $alpha, $amplitude, $shape, $tags, $phase)</make>
    <callback>set_constellation($constellation)</callback>
    <callback>set_baudRate($baudRate)</callback>
    <callback>set_numberOfTaps($numberOfTaps)</callback>
    <callback>set_alpha($alpha)</callback>
    <callback>set_amplitude($amplitude)</callback>
    <callback>set_shape($shape)</callback>
    <callback>enable_tags($tags)</callback>
    <callback>set_phase($phase)</callback>
    <param>
        <name>Samples per Symbol</name>
        <key>samplesPerSymbol</key>
        <value>1</value>
        <type>int</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Constellation</name>
        <key>constellation</key>
        <value>[1,1j,-1j,-1]</value>
        <type>complex_vector</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Baud Rate</name>
        <key>baudRate</key>
        <value>100e3</value>
        <type>real</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Taps</name>
        <key>numberOfTaps</key>
        <value>1024</value>
        <type>int</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Excess Bandwidth</name>
        <key>alpha</key>
        <value>0.5</value>
        <type>real</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Amplitude</name>
        <key>amplitude</key>
        <value>0.8</value>
        <type>real</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Shape</name>
        <key>shape</key>
        <value>0</value>
        <type>int</type>
        <option>
            <name>Rectangular</name>
            <key>0</key>
        </option>
        <option>
            <name>Root-Raised Cosine</name>
            <key>1</key>
        </option>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Trigger Tags</name>
        <key>tags</key>
        <value>False</value>
        <type>bool</type>
        <option>
            <name>Yes</name>
            <key>True</key>
        </option>
        <option>
            <name>No</name>
            <key>False</key>
        </option>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Phase</name>
        <key>phase</key>
        <value>0.0</value>
        <type>real</type>
    </param>
    <sink>
        <name>in</name>
        <type>@PYTHON_SYMBOL_TYPE@</type>
    </sink>
    <source>
        <name>out</name>
        <type>complex</type>
    </source>
    <doc>This block generates a sequence of digital pulses from a sequence of digital symbols. This is an interpolating block in that it produces a fixed quantity of of samples per symbol. The block has the following capabilities:
- Either rectangular or root-raised-cosine pulses.
- Multiple parameters in the root-raised cosine case can be configured.
- The constellation pattern can be set as a vector of complex values where the integer representation of the symbol is used as an index to said vector.
- An accumulating per-symbol phase shift can be applied to the constellation pattern for the purpose of spectral null shifting if it is so desired.
- Output signal amplitude.
- A trigger tag can be enabled to the start of every pulse for scope triggering.</doc>
</block>
